# Documentation conventions

- `docs/README.md` is the entry point â€” doc map, reading order, open questions
- `docs/architecture.md` is the source of truth for system design
- Diagrams live in `docs/diagrams/` as `.mermaid` files, referenced inline with `> **[name](diagrams/file.mermaid)**`
- Cross-references between docs use relative links: `[storage.md](storage.md)`
- Key spaces and state schemas go in `storage.md`, not `architecture.md`
- File layout and BitTorrent details go in `content.md`
- Token/fee details go in `economics.md`
- Election/takedown details go in `governance.md`
- When adding new state, update both the relevant doc AND `storage.md` key spaces
- When adding new transaction types, update `architecture.md` Transaction Types section
- Open questions go in `docs/README.md` under "Open questions and known gaps"
